DOZENS more schools in need of repairs are to benefit from a £330million boost. £330m boost for schools' upgrades DOZENS more schools in need of repairs are to benefit from a £330million boost.The extra cash is being put into the Scotland's Schools for the Future programme, which has so far given funds to schools in all 32 local authorities to improve them.Seventeen new schools are already open with 50 more due to open by March 2018.Learning Minister Alasdair Allan said: &quot;This additional funding will now allow us to almost double our original target.&quot;The projects are a welcome boost to the local economy, creating apprenticeship opportunities and construction jobs.&quot; 